<p style=3D"margin:0;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;-ms-text-size-adjust:non=
e;mso-line-height-rule:exactly;font-family:roboto, 'helvetica neue', helvet=
ica, arial, sans-serif;line-height:22.5px;color:#333333;font-size:15px">Dea=
r Benjamin,</p>
<p style=3D"margin:0;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;-ms-text-size-adjust:non=
e;mso-line-height-rule:exactly;font-family:roboto, 'helvetica neue', helvet=
ica, arial, sans-serif;line-height:22.5px;color:#333333;font-size:15px"><br=
></p>
<p style=3D"margin:0;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;-ms-text-size-adjust:non=
e;mso-line-height-rule:exactly;font-family:roboto, 'helvetica neue', helvet=
ica, arial, sans-serif;line-height:22.5px;color:#333333;font-size:15px">Thi=
s week, Cascade Policy Institute president John Charles sent a letter to th=
e members of Oregon=E2=80=99s House and Senate about Metro=E2=80=99s <a tar=
get=3D"_blank" href=3D"https://soshily.cascadepolicy.org/lt.php?x=3D4lZy~GE=
2VnGaEH77yN-7U.BxAaBRjdD1k-02X5DIUFSi58Kr-Uy7x.Nv23SRzk~w_x6vZHbFMnGZ55OKz.=
xGW.Js1E" style=3D"-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;-ms-text-size-adjust:none;=
mso-line-height-rule:exactly;text-decoration:underline;color:#0000EE;font-s=
ize:15px">Regional Rail Futures Study</a>, prepared in response to a 2024 l=
egislative mandate in <a target=3D"_blank" href=3D"https://soshily.cascadep=
olicy.org/lt.php?x=3D4lZy~GE2VnGaEH77yN-7U.BxAaBRjdD1k-02X5DIUFSi58Kr-Uy7x.=
Nv23SRzk~w_x6vZHbFMnGZ55OKz.xGW.Js1U" style=3D"-webkit-text-size-adjust:non=
e;-ms-text-size-adjust:none;mso-line-height-rule:exactly;text-decoration:un=
derline;color:#0000EE;font-size:15px">Senate Bill 5701</a>, Section 503.</p=
>
<p style=3D"margin:0;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;-ms-text-size-adjust:non=
e;mso-line-height-rule:exactly;font-family:roboto, 'helvetica neue', helvet=
ica, arial, sans-serif;line-height:22.5px;color:#333333;font-size:15px"><br=
></p>
<p style=3D"margin:0;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;-ms-text-size-adjust:non=
e;mso-line-height-rule:exactly;font-family:roboto, 'helvetica neue', helvet=
ica, arial, sans-serif;line-height:22.5px;color:#333333;font-size:15px;marg=
in-left:40px"><strong>SECTION 503. In addition to and not in lieu of any ot=
her appropriation, there is appropriated to the Department of Transportatio=
n, for the biennium ending June 30, 2025, out of the General Fund, the amou=
nt of $500,000, for distribution to the metropolitan service district organ=
ized under ORS chapter 268 to study the use of existing heavy freight rail =
assets in the Portland metropolitan area for passenger rail alternatives to=
 existing transportation modes.&nbsp;</strong></p>
<p style=3D"margin:0;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;-ms-text-size-adjust:non=
e;mso-line-height-rule:exactly;font-family:roboto, 'helvetica neue', helvet=
ica, arial, sans-serif;line-height:22.5px;color:#333333;font-size:15px"><br=
></p>
<p style=3D"margin:0;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;-ms-text-size-adjust:non=
e;mso-line-height-rule:exactly;font-family:roboto, 'helvetica neue', helvet=
ica, arial, sans-serif;line-height:22.5px;color:#333333;font-size:15px">Joh=
n attached a published <a target=3D"_blank" href=3D"https://soshily.cascade=
policy.org/lt.php?x=3D4lZy~GE2VnGaEH77yN-7U.BxAaBRjdD1k-02X5DIUFSi58Kr-Uy7x=
.Nv23SRzk~w_x6vZHbFMnGZ55OKz.xGW.Js1k" style=3D"-webkit-text-size-adjust:no=
ne;-ms-text-size-adjust:none;mso-line-height-rule:exactly;text-decoration:u=
nderline;color:#0000EE;font-size:15px">report</a> by Cascade adjunct schola=
r, Randal O=E2=80=99Toole, who reviewed the study which identifies major pr=
oblems with regional passenger rail in the Portland area, including high op=
erating costs, the need for major infrastructure improvements, congestion o=
n existing freight lines, limited high ridership along many corridors, and =
weak ridership prospects in some corridors.</p>
<p style=3D"margin:0;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;-ms-text-size-adjust:non=
e;mso-line-height-rule:exactly;font-family:roboto, 'helvetica neue', helvet=
ica, arial, sans-serif;line-height:22.5px;color:#333333;font-size:15px"><br=
></p>
<p style=3D"margin:0;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;-ms-text-size-adjust:non=
e;mso-line-height-rule:exactly;font-family:roboto, 'helvetica neue', helvet=
ica, arial, sans-serif;line-height:22.5px;color:#333333;font-size:15px">Yet=
 despite those findings, Metro declined to rule out regional rail and inste=
ad continued to encourage large-scale rail-oriented investments and additio=
nal land-use changes near freight corridors.</p>
